##A long month for the girl in Wuhan

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

Wuhan Girl Wei Wei is still not sure how her mother is infected, she can only think of one possibility: January 6, the family held a funeral for her grandfather. At the time, most people were unfazed by the news of an unexplained case of viral pneumonia. Relatives have come from all over Wuhan. After the funeral, mom had a fever, and then dad and grandma had a fever.

Grandma died on January 27; Dad died the next day. The cause of death was listed on the medical certificate as pneumonia caused by a COVID-19 infection. According to the medical certificate of death (inference) book shows that Wei Wei Wei's father and grandmother from illness to death about 12 days interval. Meanwhile, her mother was still being treated in isolation.

The interview took place on Jan. 29, the day after VIV's father died. She did not cry. Her tone was calm. She kept saying that she was "fine, " that "this is something that can be said directly, " and that "I don't have anything. ". She had been a great crier, and now she felt as if she had grown up overnight -- as if mother was still in isolation, as if her younger brother had not been able to take care of himself, as if there were so many things going on in the family that she did not have time to grieve.

Here's what Wei Wei says:

Here's what Wei Wei says:

By Luo Qian

Editor | locust tree

1

My family has 3 people infected, mother, grandmother and father. Grandma did not live the day before yesterday, died in the afternoon; father died yesterday morning, mother is now better treatment.

It was my mom who got sick in the first place, and I'm not sure how she got it. My mother seldom went to Hankou because she had to take care of my father, and she did not have direct or indirect contact with people from the south China Seafood Market. The only thing I can think of is that GRANDPA died on January 6th and there was a funeral in the house. My home in the outskirts of Wuhan, at that time, a variety of relatives from all over Wuhan rushed to eat, I guess my mother may be infected at that time. I don't know if any of my relatives have been infected, but I've got my own house to think about.

After GRANDPA's funeral, my mother had a persistent fever. On January 10, my mother went to the clinic to get a fever shot. No one said at the time how bad it was, but I knew it. On January 13, I sent my mother to the People's Hospital in the district for a check-up. She had a chest x-ray and the doctor said it was not pneumonia, i was fine. I just needed more medicine.

At that time, Dad and grandma at home, began to have a little fever. And then I thought, "well, mom gave it to dad and grandma. ". But their symptoms weren't so bad at the time, so I had to treat my mother.

January 18, I work in the company holiday, mother fever or not good, she did not sleep all night, very bad. I quickly took my mother from the outskirts of Wuhan to the city and went to the Emergency Department of the Wuhan Central Hospital in the early morning. The emergency department doctors took a CT scan of her lungs. The diagnostic report showed that the veins of her lungs had thickened, multiple Patchy and striate ground-glass opacity in both lungs. The doctor didn't say exactly what it was, but when I pressed him, he said, "it's probably COVID-19. ". And he sent us to infection for tests, and they're full of mom-like symptoms.

You know, the kits have been in short supply ever since, and it was hard to get a diagnosis on the 18th. That day we waited in line in the emergency department for a shot, more than three hours, full of fever patients, and a lot of families came over, all wearing masks. The triage table is full of people, the infusion room seats are full, the line for infusion is about 30 meters long.

The medical staff is very hard, 24 hours a day on duty, I saw in the hospital a patient's family and the doctor argued. Patients and doctors are not wrong, but there is no way, everyone is really worried, are desperate.

Because there was no bed, I opened a room in a hotel near the central hospital. Every day I took my mother to the hospital for injections. Because there was no specific medicine, my mother took an anti-pneumonia medicine for 3 days. The doctors say that's all they can do. The rest is up to the mother's own resistance.

In order to improve the mother's resistance, in addition to eating nutritious things, you can also inject Immunoglobulin, this thing is very expensive. I feel a little bit of hope to seize, to the hospital near the pharmacy to ask, normal is about 500 yuan a bottle, sold that day for 700 yuan. I also heard that there is a street in Wuhan selling this drug, go there, 550 a bottle, I bought nine bottles. The doctors at the Central Hospital recommended that the Ivig should be based on a person's weight, and the nine vials were all administered to the mother.

I asked around to help my mother find beds, always can not find, can only prepare my mother to the home side of the hospital to send. Suburban hospitals are certainly not as good as the medical facilities and environments here in the city. On January 22, I drove my mother back to the suburban hospital, half way received a phone call, Wuhan Hankou Air Force Hospital has an empty bed, I immediately turned around, to do the hospital. The doctors at the Air Force Hospital told me that I could take Ivig, but not nine at a time. That's when I realized that I had given my mom too much, but my mom was a little sick at the time, and I had no choice. I went back to buy Immunoglobulin, and the price went up again. This time, I bought 16 bottles to keep in reserve.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
People line up to buy supplies at a pharmacy in Wuhan, China Daily

2

After helping my mother in hospital, on January 23, early in the morning, I rushed back home to the suburbs to settle down my father and grandmother, both of them more and more serious fever.

Dad is hypertensive patient, apoplectic 7 years, life can not take care of oneself, Hemiplegia, have nurse to watch all the time. Dad Fat, very heavy, I can not move him, find some acquaintances to help, together to the district of the People's Hospital Dad, finally more beds, in the hospital.

At the District People's Hospital, my father and my grandmother lived in different wards in the same quarantine zone. After the stroke, Dad was a little bit like a kid, yelling every day, wanting to smoke, wanting to eat. Now he is sick, living in the ward, I am afraid of his influence on others, told him to be good, obedient, eat more. He said yes. When I left, he was in a wheelchair, waiting for his uncle to make his bed. He's tired, he's going to sleep, but when I talk to him, he answers. I remember he had a fever of close to 102, and his face was red.

From Dad's room, I went to grandma's room, see grandma wearing a mask to sleep, feel her very uncomfortable. The quilt fell down half, I give her cover, at this time, grandma opened her eyes to look at me, I called her, "grandma" . She said she was so upset, she didn't think she'd make it. All I can do is comfort her. She'll feel better if she eats more. Before she left, she told me to take care of my mother.

I actually had a feeling that this was going to be the last time. Because Dad and grandma have basic disease, dad high blood pressure, grandma has diabetes, plus old age, poor resistance, but I still hope there is a miracle. I got out of the hospital that day, and I just got in the car and I started crying, and I just kept crying. It was dark. My boyfriend and I hadn't eaten yet. We went to the supermarket and bought some bread. We sat in the car and ate. We cried while we ate. After that, we had to rush back to Wuhan. My mother was still in the hospital there.

Wuhan closed the city, I and my mother in the city, my father and grandmother in the suburbs, I drove a person to see my father and grandmother, do not know which road can go, which road can not go, these will delay time. Meanwhile, mom's GonNa need me 24 hours a day. When you have a sick person in your family who needs to be cared for and helped, that kind of helplessness... there's really nothing you can do.

They say, "true love is found in adversity. " There is another condition, "false love is found in sickness. ". You can see a lot from the outbreak. I've learned a lot in my time.

On the day of the lockdown, I had to give my dad his ID, which was an hour's drive to the highway. Because my boyfriend and I read the news the night before, and I was so anxious that I stayed up almost all night, afraid to drive, afraid to drive, afraid to drive tired, I asked my relatives for help, asked who can help with ID cards to my father, no one answered. I had no choice but to take a taxi with my boyfriend.

It was night, it was raining heavily, the road was closed, no one to pick up a single car, someone to pick up a single, and then call us back, or bargain with us, the original 200 yuan road to pay 600 yuan. Then we were lucky, met a Didi direct orders, is a young man. He dropped us off at Hankou, sealed off the entrance to the city, and told us to walk in and get a cab. Really appreciate that young man, he said he could not sleep at night, out to pick people up.

After Dad was in the hospital, my uncle stayed with him 24 hours a day, and my aunt helped him all the time. The day before yesterday, grandma left, many relatives in the group in Mourning, but dad was still alive at that time. Uncle and aunt health is not too good, I would like to which relatives to replace uncle, Take Care of Dad, but they are in the group mourning grandma. When I said I was covering for my uncle, there was no response, no word from uncle or brother.

You know, I get it, too. It's a disease that everyone used to be at risk for. But at times like this, I think of my mother's words, "you can't depend on anyone, you're on your own. " It sounds like an angry word, but now I really feel like I have to depend on myself. There's no way. There's really no way.

In the end, both dad and grandma died in isolation. I bought 20 vials of Ivig for my grandma and my dad, and they shared them. They took two days, and they used half of them. It only took two days, and they're gone. I don't know what's GonNa Happen, but the family's not allowed to follow, and the body goes straight to the funeral home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Grandma Wei Wei is under the orange tree. She said to Wei Wei: The oranges are full, you quickly bring the phone to me to take a picture of the source interviewee

3

Mom says she's better now. During her first few days in the hospital, she had a hard time moving and talking without oxygen. Now slowly you can get out of the oxygen tank and get up to do the dishes, wash clothes and eat better.

She's a survivor. She's very cooperative. When she was sick, she couldn't eat anything, but she knew she had to, and she forced herself to eat. By now, she knew what she wanted to eat, and she would order from us and have it made and delivered. Sometimes she wanted to eat beef and radish soup, sometimes it was spareribs soup, her uncle would give her stir-fry Red Vegetable Moss, she would also say, "Red Vegetable Moss do not stir-fry Salty. ".

Chinese New Year's Day, mothers take orders

Mom is a strong woman, and she knows that healing herself is the most important thing right now. Other than that, there's nothing she can do. She must be upset. Yesterday morning, I went to send something to her, before setting out heard the news of his father left, want to keep her in the dark, but the family said in the Wechat Group, I did not hide. I was worried, but when I saw her, she seemed so calm, and she told me to protect myself.

Every time I went to deliver something, the doctor and my friends said not to send it in, but I always sent it in and came out with a few words of advice.

I am 27 years old, in fact, a lot of things I do not know how to do, do not happen in their own body is not know how to do. Less than a month, GRANDPA, grandma, dad are gone, I hope mom can well. The day before yesterday, when I knew my grandma had left, it was really hard. The day before yesterday, when I knew my dad had left, I was going to drive out, and I couldn't get too emotional. I mainly worry about my mother, I can not have anything now, tears wipe on the good.

In fact, the Year of the college entrance examination, my father had a stroke, I began to feel grown up. But mom kept US safe. She kept US alive. We have a good family. We run a driving school. Dad used to work in engineering. After dad had a stroke, mom didn't make us any less financially viable. These days, I feel like I'm really growing up, and I don't want to grow up this way.

In early January, my family bought an elevator room in the city and paid for it in advance. The Elevator House was for dad's convenience. At that time, GRANDPA has gone, my mother said, grandma took care of GRANDPA for nearly 20 years, later to take grandma to enjoy the good life, and so on house decoration, we will take grandma to live together. Grandma used to cook a big dinner for Chinese New Year. The first day to the third day, the family has been very lively, many people come to New Year. On New Year's Eve this year, I turned on my IPAD for the Spring Festival gala and watched the news all the time. When you have good news, you feel a little hopeful. I can especially empathize with the family members of many patients who have shared their experiences on Weibo.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Weiwei family group chat page

These days, I sleep best the day I get my dad settled. That day, I gave my aunt my health insurance card, ID card and all kinds of things to do tests. I told her which things were with her and which were with the doctor. I made it very clear to her, but she's tired, and she forgets. I was a little broken down, crying in the ward, crying very loudly, the heart of the backlog of things out of the vent. That night, on the way back from the hospital, I fell asleep in the car, sound asleep. For the rest of the day, sleep, wake up, and wake up every hour or two. I can not sleep, also do not dare to mute, afraid of mother need what thing, send a message at midnight. In the middle received a lot of friends care, the boss gave a big red envelope, friends also red envelope, and send masks. I'll take it all. The epidemic's over. We'll see what we can do in return.

A few days ago, the weather in Wuhan was particularly bad. The weather forecast said that starting yesterday, the weather in the next few days was particularly good, the weather was fine, the mood was a little bit better, the weather was bad, just like in the TV series, the people were already miserable, and it was going to rain heavily here. I can finally understand why TV dramas and movies are like that, because I am the most sad time, it is raining in Wuhan. I posted it yesterday, and it finally came out, but dad's gone. Brother said that the night before last he went to the hospital with his uncle shift to take care of Dad, the middle of the night, dad is awake, has been talking to him, said, do not want to drag the family.

From now on, I just want to be safe and healthy. Last birthday, a good friend said I, the rat year chicken people will be too old, she helped me beg a bracelet, asked me what I hope to get, I said health. I was working so hard that I got sick, thinking it wasn't so important to make more money, it was more important to be healthy. After wearing that bracelet, I found a job, especially satisfied, in good condition, work is happy, just tell my friend, she gave me the bracelet is very clever. Friends joke. If I'd known it was gonNA work, I'd have asked for money. I said I don't want money, I want health. Now every day I go out, I wear this bracelet, I regard it as a mascot, amulet.

This situation at home doesn't allow me to be too emotional, and if I am, I have to do what needs to be done first. There's a mental illness called post-traumatic stress disorder, and I don't know if I'm like that, but maybe after this whole thing, I'm still gonNA cry. I am a very easy to shed tears, but recently on the contrary, not so much love to cry. Now Ok, this thing can be directly put out to say, I am not very excited, very resentful, it seems that there is no strength to that.

I hope there's more good news, no more bad news, and there's no way there's any more bad news at home right now. That's enough for today. I have to take my medicine, take some preventive medicine, and then go to see my mother in the afternoon.
